# Frontend Implementation Quality

- Reuse existing tokens and shared styles before introducing new hardcoded values.
- If new design tokens are needed, add them in shared variables and apply consistently.
- Keep selectors maintainable and avoid unnecessary specificity escalation.
- Maintain responsive behavior at existing breakpoints; verify mobile and desktop outcomes.
- Keep accessibility basics intact: semantic structure, alt text, focus visibility, and readable contrast.

## Assets and Placeholders

- You may replace visuals with placeholders when polish requires it.
- Clearly mark placeholder assets in code comments with concise replacement notes.
- Do not remove media without providing a styled fallback.

## Validation

- After substantive edits, run lint diagnostics on changed files and fix introduced issues.
- Report what changed by file and why each change supports the design objective.
